@startuml
' --- whole-map provenance: cycle that introduced each @id ---
' @cycle(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE, 0007)
' @cycle(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT, 0007)
' @cycle(USE-DEPLOY-PURPOSE, 0016)
' @cycle(USE-DEPLOY-ACCESS-CHECK, 0016)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-PURPOSE)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-ACCESS-CHECK)
'
' Current-side use cases for /mdd-deploy, derived from the implemented
' code: templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL + its WORKFLOW_SKILLS entry, the
' .claude/.codex/skills/mdd-deploy/SKILL.md mirrors materialized by
' `mdd init`, the extended templates::MDD_RENDER_SKILL step, and
' .mdd/docs/deploy-profile.md. The skill is a standalone utility,
' a sibling of /mdd-render, and is NOT routed into any gate.
'
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE, "Implemented: /mdd-deploy is registered as a WORKFLOW_SKILLS entry and materialized into .claude/.codex/skills/mdd-deploy/SKILL.md. Its body instructs the agent to produce a deployment diagram + generated Bicep + a STOP-gated runbook for azure-container-apps, executing no deploy command.")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT, "Implemented: templates::MDD_RENDER_SKILL gained a step instructing /mdd-render to rasterize .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml to .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg. Additive, non-gating.")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-PURPOSE, "Cycle 0016: before any purpose-driven default, /mdd-deploy confirms dev/staging/prod (no silent default) and surfaces purpose-appropriate sizing/posture options for the operator to confirm; secure-by-default preserved.")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-ACCESS-CHECK, "Cycle 0016: before emitting, /mdd-deploy accounts for who reads AND writes every secured store, each with an admitted network path; a read-but-never-written store or a writer with no path is surfaced as a blocking question.")
title /mdd-deploy deployment guidance — use cases (current)

left to right direction

actor "Operator" as Op

rectangle "mdd toolchain (utility, outside the parity gate)" {
  usecase "Guide an Azure Container Apps\ndeployment via a diagram,\nrunbook, and generated IaC" as Guide
  usecase "Inspect the generated\ndeployment diagram as SVG" as Inspect
  usecase "Confirm the deployment PURPOSE\n(dev/staging/prod) before any\npurpose-driven default — no silent default" as Purpose
  usecase "Account for who READS and WRITES\nevery secured store (identity + admitted\npath) before emitting — surface holes" as AccessCheck
}

Op --> Guide
Op --> Inspect
Op --> Purpose
Op --> AccessCheck

Guide ..> Inspect : <<extend>>
Guide ..> Purpose : <<include>>
Guide ..> AccessCheck : <<include>>

note bottom of Guide
  Implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL:
  v1 supports only azure-container-apps
  (../atlas-ate-server); any other target is
  rejected. Reads MDD models + the target repo
  read-only, pauses on ambiguity, writes the
  deployment diagram + runbook + generated infra,
  then reports and STOPS. Never runs az/docker/
  brew. The diagram stereotypes are documentation
  only — NOT the gated security-marker parity
  mechanism. Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of Inspect
  Not a gate. /mdd-validate, /mdd-review and the
  /mdd-cycle parity loop never read .mdd/deploy/.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT.
end note

note bottom of Purpose
  Cycle 0016: mandatory <<include>>; no purpose-driven
  default until dev/staging/prod is confirmed (no silent
  default). Surfaces sizing/posture options; operator
  confirms; secure-by-default preserved.
  Constrained by OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-PURPOSE.
end note

note bottom of AccessCheck
  Cycle 0016: mandatory <<include>>; every secured store
  needs a named reader AND writer with an admitted
  network path, else surfaced as a blocking question.
  Constrained by OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-ACCESS-COMPLETE.
end note
@enduml
